  "conclusion": {
    "title": "Conclusion & Comparison",
    "partials": {
      "pro": {
        "label": "Strengths",
        "items": [
          {
            "text": "Diversification of production: terracing makes cultivation of new cash crops possible: flax (for linseed oil), pears, apples, apricots, water melon; all these give high returns and thus make terrace construction profitable."
          },
          {
            "text": "Improvements of farmers’ living standard and decline in poverty stricken population"
          },
          {
            "text": "Reduced erosion, reduced loss of rainwater through runoff (increased in water use efficiency) and reduced fertility loss due to reduced slope angle and length"
          },
          {
            "text": "Increased soil moisture"
          },
          {
            "text": "Increased crop production (before 1983 hunger and starvation in the area)"
          },
          {
            "text": "Easier field operations: the level terrace is easier to cultivate than the original hill slope"
          }
        ]
      },
      "contra": {
        "label": "Weaknesses/ disadvantages/ risks and how they can be overcome",
        "items": [
          {
            "text": "Decrease in production in first year",
            "subtext": "Apply manure and fertilizer."
          },
          {
            "text": "Terrace riser can be destroyed by storms – and, sometimes, rodent holes",
            "subtext": "Good and timely repair and maintenance: planting upper parts of the risers with grass, bushes or even trees help to stabilise the risers but can lead to competition with the crop for water."
          },
          {
            "text": "High cost/input for construction and establishment",
            "subtext": "Given the high erodibility of the soil and the steep slopes there is no real alternatives to labour-intensive terracing."
          },
          {
            "text": "High loss of soil moisture due to evaporation from the soil surface. Wind erosion due to tillage",
            "subtext": "Protect soil surface for example by conservation agriculture – comprising permanent cover, crop rotation, reduced tillage – could be supplementary agronomic and vegetative options."
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  },
